==''Fell–fail'' merger==
The same two regions show a closely related merger, namely the '''''fell–fail'' merger''' of {{IPA|/ɛ/}} and {{IPA|/eɪ/}} before {{IPA|/l/}} that occurs in some varieties of [[Southern American English]] making ''fell'' and ''fail'' homophones. In addition to North Carolina and Texas, these mergers are found sporadically in other Southern states and in the Midwest and West.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ling.upenn.edu/phono_atlas/maps/Map7.html |title=Map 7 |publisher=Ling.upenn.edu |date= |accessdate=2011-03-02}}</ref><ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20061028164228/http://www.ling.upenn.edu/phonoatlas/Atlas_chapters/Ch9/Ch9.html</ref>

